  "text": "The Apache Kafka consumer group coordinator implements a state machine for managing group membership and rebalancing. The implementation is split between Classic groups (traditional protocol) and Modern groups (consumer protocol, share protocol, and streams protocol).\n\n**Classic Group State Machine:**\nThe core state machine is defined in `ClassicGroupState.java` (group-coordinator/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/coordinator/group/classic/) with five states:\n1. EMPTY - Group has no members, waiting for new members to join\n2. PREPARING_REBALANCE - Group is in the join phase, collecting join requests from members\n3. COMPLETING_REBALANCE - Group is in the sync phase, awaiting assignments from the leader\n4. STABLE - All members have joined and synced, group is operational\n5. DEAD - Group metadata is being removed\n\nThe valid state transitions are enforced through the `validPreviousStates` set in `ClassicGroupState`, defining the valid transitions:\n- EMPTY → PREPARING_REBALANCE\n- PREPARING_REBALANCE → COMPLETING_REBALANCE or EMPTY\n- COMPLETING_REBALANCE → STABLE\n- STABLE/PREPARING_REBALANCE/COMPLETING_REBALANCE/EMPTY → DEAD\n\n**Join Phase Implementation:**\nMember join state is tracked in `ClassicGroupMember.java` with methods `isAwaitingJoin()` which checks if `awaitingJoinFuture` is set. When members send join requests, the `classicGroupJoin()` method in `GroupMetadataManager.java` processes them and manages the group's transition to PREPARING_REBALANCE. The flow calls `addMemberThenRebalanceOrCompleteJoin()` and `maybePrepareRebalanceOrCompleteJoin()` to coordinate the state transitions.\n\n**Sync Phase Implementation:**\nMember sync state is tracked with `isAwaitingSync()` checking if `awaitingSyncFuture` is set. The `classicGroupSync()` method in `GroupMetadataManager.java` handles sync requests from members. Once all members have synced with their assignments, the group transitions from COMPLETING_REBALANCE to STABLE.\n\n**State Transitions:**\nState transitions are managed through the `transitionTo()` method in `ClassicGroup.java`, which enforces valid transitions and tracks both current and previous states. Invalid transitions throw an `IllegalStateException`.\n\n**Modern Groups:**\nModern consumer groups (`ConsumerGroup.java` in modern/consumer/) implement their own state machine with states: EMPTY, ASSIGNING, RECONCILING, STABLE, DEAD. Member states are defined in `MemberState.java` (modern/) with states like STABLE, UNRELEASED_PARTITIONS, UNREVOKED_PARTITIONS, JOINING. Similar patterns are implemented for ShareGroups (`ShareGroup.java`) and StreamsGroups (`StreamsGroup.java`), each with their own state enums and member state tracking.\n\nThe coordinator service (`GroupCoordinatorService.java`) and main coordinator (`GroupCoordinator.java`) orchestrate these state machines by routing join and sync requests to the appropriate handlers in `GroupMetadataManager.java`, which then manages the group state transitions based on member responses and timeout conditions."
